<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The revision to the existing alternate standard provides types of ATCT construction and methods of operation which
enhance the fire detection and notification, fire resistance, smoke control, and emergency response features for
ATCTs. These features provide early warning of the presence of fire or smoke, flame and smoke spread control, and automatic
notification of emergency response units such that a level of fire safety equivalent to two means of egress are afforded
ATCT occupants.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
FAA contends that the alternate standard provides equivalent or greater protection for the affected employees because
of enhancements such as, but not limited to:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;An ATCT stairway smoke control system;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Fire resistant rated materials for stairway enclosures and openings;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Self-closing or automatic fire doors;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;ATCT fire alarm system wiring in accordance with NFPA 72 reliability standards;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Automatic smoke detection;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Automatic fire detection, alarm, and signaling systems with automatic fire department and ATCT notification
and ATCT cab annunciator panels with battery backup;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Prohibition of storage of high hazard materials or use of more then minimal amounts of high hazard materials
for specific duties;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Occupancy above the level of exit discharge only be able-bodied persons;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Prescribed quality and type of interior finish materials;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Specified levels of fire resistant rated opening protective to base buildings.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Commenters are requested to comment on FAA's finding of equivalency as well as on the appropriateness of the enhancements.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Comments are requested on the following:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Is an alternate standard necessary, or are technologies such that two means of egress are possible in ATCTs?
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
