<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
12. Other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Additional provisions in the 1994 proposed rule (particularly those that differ from the 1988 proposed rule) are
addressed in the discussion of public comments on the 1988 proposed rule set forth in section VII of this preamble.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Documents in Other Languages. One additional provision included in the 1994 proposed rule is a requirement that for
any document or notice that the rule requires the responsible entity (housing authority, project owner, mortgagee)
to provide an applicant or tenant or to obtain the signature of the applicant or tenant, the responsible entity, where
feasible, is to provide such document in a language that is understood by the applicant or tenant if he or she is not proficient
in English. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Nondiscrimination Requirements. The 1994 proposed rule includes a provision that restricts the responsible entity
