Housing Act (42 U.S.C. 3601&hyph;3619), Title VI of the Civil Rights of 1964 (42 U.S.C. 2000d&hyph;2000d&hyph;5),
and section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 (29 U.S.C. 794). Such unlawful actions include determinations of
eligibility and ineligibility, using different requirements to ascertain that eligibility or ineligibility,
and treating persons differently, if those actions are based on such factors as language, country of origin, or family
associations. 
