<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) For noncitizens who are 62 years of age or older or who will be 62 years of age or older and receiving assistance under
a covered program on [insert the effect date of the final rule], the evidence consists of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A signed declaration of eligible immigration status; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Proof of age document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) For all other noncitizens, the evidence consists of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A signed declaration of eligible immigration status; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The INS documents listed in &sect;200.184; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A signed verification form. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Declaration. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) For each family member, the family must submit to the project owner a written declaration, signed under penalty
of perjury, by which the family member declares whether he or she is a U.S. citizen or a noncitizen with eligible immigration
status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For each adult, the declaration must be signed by the adult. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For each child, the declaration must be signed by an adult residing in the assisted dwelling unit who is responsible
for the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The written declaration may be incorporated as part of the application for housing assistance or may constitute
a separate document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Verification consent form
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Who signs. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each noncitizen who declares eligible immigration status must sign a verification consent form as follows. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For each adult, the form must be signed by the adult. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For each child, the form must be signed by an adult residing in the assisted dwelling unit who is responsible for
the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by project owner. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The verification consent form shall provide that evidence of eligible immigration status may be released by the project
owner without responsibility for the further use or transmission of the evidence by the entity receiving it, to:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) HUD, as required by HUD; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The INS; and, if applicable; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Another Federal agency, or a State or local government agency in accordance with Federal, State or local law
that requires the release of the evidence to that agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by HUD. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The verification consent form also shall notify the individual of the possible release of evidence of eligible immigration
status by HUD. Evidence of eligible immigration status shall only be released to the INS for purposes of establishing
eligibility for financial assistance and not for any other purpose. HUD is not responsible for the further use or transmission
of the evidence or other information by the INS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Individuals who do not contend that they have eligible status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If one or more members of a family elect not to contend that they have eligible immigration status, and other members
of the family establish their citizenship or eligible immigration status, the family may be eligible for prorated
assistance under &sect;200.188, despite the fact that no declaration or documentation of eligible status is submitted
for one or more members of the family. The family must, however, identify to the project owner, the family member (or
members) who will elect not to contend that he or she has eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notification of requirements of section 214
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When notice is to be issued. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by
this section, or to elect not to contend that one has eligible status, as provided by paragraph (e) of this section,
shall be given by the project owner as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicant's notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each applicant at the time
of application for assistance. Applicants whose applications are pending on [insert the effective date of the final
rule] shall be notified of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status as soon as possible after [insert
the effective date of the final rule]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Tenant's notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each tenant at the time of,
and together with, the project owner's notice of regular reexamination of tenant income, but not later than one year
following [insert the effective date of the final rule]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Timing of mortgagor's notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A mortgagor receiving section 235 assistance must be notified of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status
in accordance with &sect;235.13(b)(2).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Form and content of notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The notice shall: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) State that financial assistance is contingent upon the submission and verification, as appropriate, of evidence
of citizenship or eligible immigration status as required by paragraph (a) of this section; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Describe the type of evidence that must be submitted, and state the time period in which that evidence must be submitted
(see paragraph (g) of this section concerning when evidence must be submitted); and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940825-1-00055 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940825-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(iii) State that assistance will be prorated, denied or terminated, as appropriate, upon a final determination of
ineligibility after all appeals have been exhausted (see &sect;200.186 concerning INS appeal, and informal hearing
process by the project owner) or, if appeals are not pursued, at a time to be specified in accordance with HUD requirements.
Tenants also shall be informed of how to obtain assistance under the preservation of families provisions of &sect;200.187.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When evidence of eligible status is required to be submitted. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The project owner shall require evidence of eligible status to be submitted at the times specified in paragraph (g)
of this section, subject to any extension granted in accordance with paragraph (h) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicants. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For applicants, project owners must ensure that evidence of eligible status is submitted not later than the date the
project owner anticipates or has knowledge that verification of other aspects of eligibility for assistance will
occur (see &sect;200.185(a)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Tenants. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For tenants (i.e., persons already receiving the benefit of assistance in a covered program on [insert the effective
date of the final rule]), evidence of eligible status is required to be submitted as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For financial assistance in the form of rent supplement payments or section 236 basic rent tenancy or rental assistance
payments, the tenant shall, in accordance with the provisions of &sect;&sect;215.55(a) and 236.80(a) of this chapter,
submit the required evidence at the first regular reexamination after [insert the effective date of the final rule].

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For financial assistance in the form of section 235 assistance payments, the mortgagor shall submit the required
evidence in accordance with &sect;235.13(c) of this chapter. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
New occupants of assisted units. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For any new occupant of an assisted unit (e.g., a new family member comes to reside in the assisted unit), the required
evidence shall be submitted at the first interim or regular reexamination following the person's occupancy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Changing participation in a HUD program. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Whenever a family applies for admission to a program covered by this subpart, evidence of eligible status is required
to be submitted in accordance with the requirements of this subpart unless the family already has submitted the evidence
to the project owner for a covered program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
One-time evidence requirement for continuous occupancy. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For each family member, the family is required to submit evidence of eligible status only one time during continuously
assisted occupancy under any covered program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Extensions of time to submit evidence of eligible status
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When extension must be granted. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The project owner shall extend the time, provided in paragraph (g) of this section, to submit evidence of eligible
immigration status if the family member: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Submits the declaration required under &sect;200.183(a) certifying that any person for whom required evidence
has not been submitted is a noncitizen with eligible immigration status; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Certifies that the evidence needed to support a claim of eligible immigration status is temporarily unavailable,
additional time is needed to obtain and submit the evidence; and prompt and diligent efforts will be undertaken to
obtain the evidence. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Prohibition on indefinite extension period. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any extension of time, if granted, shall be for a specific period of time. The additional time provided should be sufficient
to allow the individual the time to obtain the evidence needed. The project owner's determination of the length of
the extension needed shall be based on the circumstances of the individual case. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Grant or denial of extension to be in writing. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The project owner's decision to grant or deny an extension as provided in paragraph (h)(1) of this section shall be
issued to the family by written notice. If the extension is granted, the notice shall specify the extension period
granted. If the extension is denied, the notice shall explain the reasons for denial of the extension. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Failure to submit evidence or to establish eligible status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If the family fails to submit required evidence of eligible immigration status within the time period specified in
the notice, or any extension granted in accordance with paragraph (h) of this section, or if the evidence is timely
submitted but fails to establish eligible immigration status, the project owner shall proceed to deny, prorate or
terminate assistance, or provide continued assistance or temporary deferral of termination of assistance, as appropriate,
in accordance with the provisions of &sect;&sect;200.186 and 200.187. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;200.184 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Documents of eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A project owner shall request and review original documents of eligible immigration status. The project owner shall
retain photocopies of the documents for its own records and return the original documents to the family. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Acceptable evidence of eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The original of one of the following documents is acceptable evidence of eligible immigration status, subject to
verification in accordance with &sect;200.185. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Form I&hyph;551, Alien Registration Receipt Card (for permanent resident aliens); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Form I&hyph;94, Arrival-Departure Record, with one of the following annotations: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) ``Admitted as Refugee Pursuant to section 207''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) ``Section 208'' or ``Asylum''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) ``Section 243(h)'' or ``Deportation stayed by Attorney General''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) ``Paroled Pursuant to Sec. 212(d)(5) of the INA''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If Form I&hyph;94, Arrival-Departure Record, is not annotated, then accompanied by one of the following documents:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A final court decision granting asylum (but only if no appeal is taken); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
