<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Events causing denial or termination of assistance._
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Assistance to an applicant shall be denied, and a tenant's assistance shall be terminated, in accordance with the
procedures of this section, upon the occurrence of any of the following events: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Evidence of citizenship (i.e., the declaration) and eligible immigration status is not submitted by the date
specified in &sect;200.183(g) or by the expiration of any extension granted in accordance with &sect;200.183(h);
or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Evidence of citizenship and eligible immigration status is timely submitted, but INS primary and secondary
verification does not verify eligible immigration status of a family member; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The family does not pursue INS appeal or informal hearing rights as provided in this section; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) INS appeal and informal hearing rights are pursued, but the final appeal or hearing decisions are decided against
the family member. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Termination of assisted occupancy. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For termination of assisted occupancy, see paragraph (i) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of denial or termination of assistance. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The notice of denial or termination of assistance shall advise the family: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) That financial assistance will be denied or terminated, and provide a brief explanation of the reasons for the
proposed denial or termination of assistance; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) That the family may be eligible for proration of assistance as provided under &sect;200.188; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) In the case of a tenant, the criteria and procedures for obtaining relief under the preservation of families provision
in &sect;200.187; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) That the family has a right to request an appeal to the INS of the results of secondary verification of immigration
status and to submit additional documentation or a written explanation in support of the appeal in accordance with
the procedures of paragraph (e) of this section;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) That the family has a right to request an informal hearing with the project owner either upon completion of the INS
appeal or in lieu of the INS appeal as provided in paragraph (f) of this section; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) For applicants, the notice shall advise that assistance may not be delayed until the conclusion of the INS appeal
process, but assistance may be delayed during the pendency of the informal hearing process. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Appeal by applicant to the INS._
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Submission of request for appeal to project owner. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Upon receipt of notification by the project owner that INS secondary verification failed to confirm eligible immigration
status, the family may request an appeal to the INS by communicating that request to the project owner within 14 days
of the date the project owner mails or delivers the notice under paragraph (d) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Extension of time to request an appeal. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The project owner shall extend the period of time for requesting an appeal (for a specified period) upon good cause
shown. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Forwarding the appeal to INS. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If the family requests an appeal to the INS, the project owner shall forward to the designated INS office any additional
documentation or written explanation provided by the family in support of the appeal. This material must include
a copy of the INS document verification request form G&hyph;845S (used to process the secondary verification request)
and a cover letter indicating that the family is requesting an appeal of the INS immigration status verification results.
(Form G&hyph;845S is available from the local INS Office.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Decision by INS._
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When decision will be issued. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The INS will issue to the project owner a decision within 30 days of its receipt of documentation concerning the family's
appeal of the verification of immigration status. If, for any reason, the INS is unable to issue a decision within the
30 day time period, the INS will inform the project owner of the reasons for the delay, and the project owner will inform
the family of the reasons for the delay.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notification of INS decision and of informal hearing procedures. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
When the project owner receives the INS decision, the project owner shall notify the family of the INS determination,
of the reasons for the determination, and of the family's right to request an informal hearing on the PHA's ineligibility
determination in accordance with the procedures of paragraph (f) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
No delay, denial, reduction, or termination of assistance until completion of INS appeal process; direct appeal
to INS. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Pending the completion of the INS appeal under this section, assistance may not be delayed, denied, reduced or terminated
on the basis of immigration status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Informal hearing._
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When request for hearing is to be made. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
After notification of the INS decision on appeal, or in lieu of request of appeal to the INS, the family may request that
the project owner provide a hearing. This request must be made either within 14 days of the date the project owner mails
or delivers the notice under paragraph (d) of this section, or within 14 days of the mailing of the INS appeal decision
issued in accordance with paragraph (e) of this section (established by the date of postmark). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Extension of time to request hearing. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The project owner shall extend the period of time for requesting a hearing (for a specified period) upon good cause
shown. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Informal hearing procedures. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A family who submits a timely request for a hearing with the project owner shall have an opportunity for: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Hearing before an impartial individual. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be provided a hearing before any person(s) designated by the project owner (including an officer
or employee of the project owner), other than a person who made or approved the decision under review, and other than
a person who is a subordinate of the person who made or approved the decision; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Examination of evidence. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be provided the opportunity to examine and copy at the individual's expense, at a reasonable time
in advance of the hearing, any documents in the possession of the project owner pertaining to the family's eligibility
status, or in the possession of the INS (as permitted by INS requirements), including any records and regulations
that may be relevant to the hearing; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Presentation of evidence and arguments in support of eligible status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be provided the opportunity to present evidence and arguments in support of eligible status. Evidence
may be considered without regard to admissibility under the rules of evidence applicable to judicial proceedings;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Controverting evidence of the project owner. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be provided the opportunity to controvert evidence relied upon by the project owner and to confront
and cross-examine all witnesses on whose testimony or information the project owner relies; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Representation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be entitled to be represented by an attorney, or other designee, at the family's expense, and to have
such person make statements on the family's behalf; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Interpretive services. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be entitled to arrange for an interpreter to attend the hearing, at the expense of the family or project
owner, as may be agreed upon by both parties; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Hearing to be recorded. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The family shall be entitled to have the hearing recorded by audiotape (a transcript of the hearing may, but is not required
to, be provided by the project owner). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Hearing decision. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The project owner shall provide the family with a written final decision, based solely on the facts presented at the
hearing, within 14 days of the date of the informal hearing. The decision shall state the basis for the decision. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Judicial relief. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A decision against a family member, issued in accordance with paragraphs (e) or (f) of this section, does not preclude
the family from exercising the right, that may otherwise be available, to seek redress directly through judicial
procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
