<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) For noncitizens who are 62 years of age or older or who will be 62 years of age or older and receiving assistance under
a section 214 covered program on [insert the effective date of the final rule], the evidence consists of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A signed declaration of eligible immigration status; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Proof of age document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) For all other noncitizens, the evidence consists of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A signed declaration of eligible immigration status; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The INS documents listed in &sect;812.7; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A signed verification consent form. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Declaration.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For each family member, the family must submit to the responsible entity a written declaration, signed under penalty
of perjury, by which the family member declares whether he or she is a U.S. citizen or a noncitizen with eligible immigration
status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) For each adult, the declaration must be signed by the adult. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) For each child, the declaration must be signed by an adult residing in the assisted dwelling unit who is responsible
for the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Verification consent form
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Who signs.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Each noncitizen who declares eligible immigration status, must sign a verification consent form as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For each adult, the form must be signed by the adult. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For each child, the form must be signed by an adult member of the family residing in the assisted dwelling unit who
is responsible for the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by responsible entity.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The verification consent form shall provide that evidence of eligible immigration status may be released by the responsible
entity, without responsibility for the further use or transmission of the evidence by the entity receiving it, to:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) HUD as required by HUD; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The INS; and, if applicable; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Another Federal agency, or a State or local government agency in accordance with Federal, State or local law
that requires the release of the evidence to that agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by HUD.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The verification consent form also shall notify the individual of the possible release of evidence of eligible immigration
status by HUD. Evidence of eligible immigration status shall only be released to the INS for purposes of establishing
eligibility for financial assistance and not for any other purpose. HUD is not responsible for the further use or transmission
of the evidence or other information by the INS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Individuals who do not contend to have eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If one or more members of a family elect not to contend that they have eligible immigration status and the other members
of the family establish their citizenship or eligible immigration status, the family may be considered for prorated
assistance under &sect;812.11 despite the fact that no declaration or documentation of eligible status is submitted
by one or more members of the family. The family must, however, identify to the responsible entity, the family member
(or members) who will elect not to contend that he or she has eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notification of requirements of section 214
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When notice is to be issued.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by
this section, or to elect not to contend that one has eligible immigration status, as allowed by paragraph (e) of this
section, shall be given by the responsible entity as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicant's notice.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each applicant at the time
of application for financial assistance. Families whose applications are pending on [insert the effective date
of the final rule] shall be notified of the requirements to submit evidence of eligible status as soon as possible after
[insert the effective date of the final rule]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice to families already receiving assistance.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For a family in occupancy on [insert the effective date of the final rule] notification of the requirement to submit
evidence of eligible status shall be given to each at the time of, and together with, the responsible entity's notice
of the first regular reexamination after that date, but not later than one year following [insert the effective date
of the final rule]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Form and content of notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The notice shall: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) State that financial assistance is contingent upon the submission and verification, as appropriate, of the evidence
of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by this section; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Describe the type of evidence that must be submitted and state the time period in which that evidence must be submitted
(see paragraph (g) of this section concerning when evidence must be submitted); and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) State that assistance will be prorated, denied or terminated, as appropriate, upon a final determination of
ineligibility after all appeals have been exhausted (see &sect;812.9 concerning INS appeal, and informal hearing
process) or, if appeals are not pursued, at a time to be specified in accordance with HUD requirements. Families already
receiving assistance also shall be informed of how to obtain assistance under the preservation of families provisions
of &sect;812.10. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When evidence of eligible status is required to be submitted.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The responsible entity shall require evidence of eligible status to be submitted at the times specified in paragraph
(g) of this section, subject to any extension granted in accordance with paragraph (h) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicants.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For applicants, the responsible entity must ensure that evidence of eligible status is submitted not later than the
date the responsible entity anticipates or has knowledge that verification of other aspects of eligibility for assistance
will occur (see &sect;812.8(a)).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
