<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Families already receiving assistance.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For a family already receiving the benefit of assistance in a covered program on [insert the effective date of the final
rule], the required evidence shall be submitted at the first regular reexamination after [insert the effective date
of the final rule], in accordance with program requirements. (See &sect;&sect;850.151, 880.603, 881.603, 882.212,
882.515, 883.704, 884.124, 886.124, 886.324, or 887.357 of this chapter.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
New occupants of assisted units.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For any new family members, the required evidence shall be submitted at the first interim or regular reexamination
following the person's occupancy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Changing participation in a HUD program.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Whenever a family applies for admission to a section 214 covered program, evidence of eligible status is required
to be submitted in accordance with the requirements of this part unless the family already has submitted the evidence
to the responsible entity for a covered program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
One-time evidence requirement for continuous occupancy.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For each family member, the family is required to submit evidence of eligible status one time during continuously
assisted occupancy under any covered program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Extensions of time to submit evidence of eligible status
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When extension must be granted.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The responsible entity shall extend the time provided in paragraph (g) of this section, to submit evidence of eligible
immigration status if the family member: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Submits the declaration required under &sect;812.6(b) certifying that any person for whom required evidence
has not been submitted is a noncitizen with eligible immigration status; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Certifies that the evidence needed to support a claim of eligible immigration status is temporarily unavailable,
additional time is needed to obtain and submit the evidence, and prompt and diligent efforts will be undertaken to
obtain the evidence. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Prohibition on indefinite extension period.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Any extension of time, if granted, shall be for a specific period of time. The additional time provided should be sufficient
to allow the family the time to obtain the evidence needed. The responsible entity's determination of the length of
the extension needed shall be based on the circumstances of the individual case. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Grant or denial of extension to be in writing.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The responsible entity's decision to grant or deny an extension as provided in paragraph (h)(1) of this section shall
be issued to the family by written notice. If the extension is granted, the notice shall specify the extension period
granted. If the extension is denied, the notice shall explain the reasons for denial of the extension. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Failure to submit evidence or establish eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If the family fails to submit required evidence of eligible immigration status within the time period specified in
the notice, or any extension granted in accordance with paragraph (h) of this section, or if the evidence is timely
submitted but fails to establish eligible immigration status, the responsible entity shall proceed to deny, prorate
or terminate assistance, or provide continued assistance or temporary deferral of termination of assistance, as
appropriate, in accordance with the provisions of &sect;&sect;812.9 and 812.10 respectively. For all section 8
programs, denial or termination of assistance shall be in accordance with the procedures of &sect;812.9. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;812.7 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Documents of eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A responsible entity shall request and review original documents of eligible immigration status. The responsible
entity shall retain photocopies of the documents for its own records and return the original documents to the family.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Acceptable evidence of eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The original of one of the following documents is acceptable evidence of eligible immigration status, subject to
verification in accordance with &sect;812.8: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Form I&hyph;551, Alien Registration Receipt Card (for permanent resident aliens); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Form I&hyph;94, Arrival-Departure Record, with one of the following annotations: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) ``Admitted as Refugee Pursuant to Section 207''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) ``Section 208'' or ``Asylum''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) ``Section 243(h)'' or ``Deportation stayed by Attorney General''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) ``Paroled Pursuant to Sec. 212(d)(5) of the INA''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If Form I&hyph;94, Arrival-Departure Record, is not annotated, then accompanied by one of the following documents:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A final court decision granting asylum (but only if no appeal is taken); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A letter from an INS asylum officer granting asylum (if application is filed on or after October 1, 1990) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
or
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 from an INS district director granting asylum (if application filed before October 1, 1990); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A court decision granting withholding or deportation; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) A letter from an INS asylum officer granting withholding of deportation (if application filed on or after October
1, 1990). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Form I&hyph;688, Temporary Resident Card, which must be annotated ``Section 245A'' or ``Section 210''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Form I&hyph;688B, Employment Authorization Card, which must be annotated ``Provision of Law 274a.12(11)''
or ``Provision of Law 274a.12''; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) A receipt issued by the INS indicating that an application for issuance of a replacement document in one of the above-listed
categories has been made and the applicant's entitlement to the document has been verified; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
