<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Submission of evidence of citizenship or eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Eligibility for assistance or continued assistance under a Section 214 covered program is contingent upon a family's
submission to the IHA of the documents described in paragraph (e)(2) of this section for each family member. If one
or more family members do not have citizenship or eligible immigration status, the members may exercise the election
not to contend to have eligible immigration status as provided in paragraph (f) of this section, and the provisions
of paragraph (r) of this section shall apply. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Evidence of citizenship or eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each family, regardless of age, must submit the following evidence to the IHA: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For citizens, the evidence consists of a signed declaration of U.S. citizenship; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For noncitizens who are 62 years of age or older or who will be 62 years of age or older and receiving assistance under
a Section 214 covered program on 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
[insert the effective date of the final rule]
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
, the evidence consists of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) A signed declaration of eligible immigration status; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Proof of age document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) For all other noncitizens, the evidence consists of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) A signed declaration of eligible immigration status; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The INS documents listed in paragraph (k)(2) of this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) A signed verification consent form. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Declaration. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For each family member, the family must submit to the IHA a written declaration, signed under penalty of perjury, by
which the family member declares whether he or she is a U.S. citizen or a noncitizen with eligible immigration status.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For each adult, the declaration must be signed by the adult.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For each child, the declaration must be signed by an adult residing in the assisted dwelling unit who is responsible
for the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Verification consent form
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Who signs. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each noncitizen who declares eligible immigration status, must sign a verification consent form as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) For each adult, the form must be signed by the adult. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) For each child, the form must be signed by an adult member of the family residing in the assisted dwelling unit who
is responsible for the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by IHA. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The verification consent form shall provide that evidence of eligible immigration status may be released by the IHA,
without responsibility for the further use or transmission of the evidence by the entity receiving it, to: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) HUD as required by HUD; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The INS; and, if applicable, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Another Federal agency, or a State or local government agency in accordance with Federal, State or local law that
requires the release of the evidence to that agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by HUD. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The verification consent form also shall notify the individual of the possible release of evidence of eligible immigration
status by HUD. Evidence of eligible immigration status shall only be released to the INS for purposes of establishing
eligibility for financial assistance and not for any other purpose. HUD is not responsible for the further use or transmission
of the evidence or other information by the INS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Individuals who do not contend to have eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If one or more members of a family elect not to contend that they have eligible immigration status and the other members
of the family establish their citizenship or eligible immigration status, the family may be considered for prorated
assistance under paragraph (s) of this section despite the fact that no declaration or documentation of eligible
status is submitted by one or more members of the family. The family must, however, identify to the IHA, the family member
(or members) who will elect not to contend that he or she has eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notification of requirements of Section 214_
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When notice is to be issued. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by
this section, or to elect not to contend that one has eligible immigration status, as allowed by paragraph (f) of this
section, shall be given by the IHA as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicant's notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each applicant at the time
of application for financial assistance. Families whose applications are pending on 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
[insert the effective date of the final rule] 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
shall be notified of the requirements to submit evidence of eligible status as soon as possible after 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
[insert the effective date of the final rule]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Notice to families already receiving assistance. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For a family in occupancy on 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
[insert the effective date of the final rule]
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
, notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each at the time of, and together
with, the IHA's notice of the first regular reexamination after that date, but not later than one year following 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
[insert the effective date of the final rule].
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Form and content of notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The notice shall: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) State that financial assistance is contingent upon the submission and verification, as appropriate, of the evidence
of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Describe the type of evidence that must be submitted and state the time period in which that evidence must be submitted
(see paragraph (h) of this section concerning when evidence must be submitted); and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



