<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(iii) State that assistance will be prorated, denied or terminated, as appropriate, upon a final determination of
ineligibility after all appeals have been exhausted (see paragraph (n) of this section concerning INS appeal, and
paragraph (o) of this section concerning IHA informal hearing process) or, if appeals are not pursued, at a time to
be specified in accordance with HUD requirements. Families already receiving assistance also shall be informed
of how to obtain assistance under the preservation of families provisions of paragraph (r) of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
When evidence of eligible status is required to be submitted. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The IHA shall require evidence of eligible status to be submitted at the times specified in paragraph (h) of this section
subject to any extension granted in accordance with paragraph (i) of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicants. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For applicants, the IHA must ensure that evidence of eligible status is submitted not later than the date the IHA anticipates
or has knowledge that verification of other aspects of eligibility for assistance will occur (see paragraph (l) of
this section).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Families already receiving assistance. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For a family already receiving the benefit of assistance in a covered program on [insert the effective date of the final
rule], the required evidence shall be submitted at the first regular reexamination after [insert the effective date
of the final rule], in accordance with program requirements.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
New occupants of assisted units. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For any new family members, the required evidence shall be submitted at the first interim or regular reexamination
following the person's occupancy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Changing participation in a HUD program. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Whenever a family applies for admission to a Section 214 covered program, evidence of eligible status is required
to be submitted in accordance with the requirements of this part unless the family already has submitted the evidence
to the IHA for a covered program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
One-time evidence requirement for continuous occupancy. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For each family member, the family is required to submit evidence of eligible status one time during continuously
assisted occupancy under any covered program.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Extensions of time to submit evidence of eligible status_
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
 When extension must be granted. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The IHA shall extend the time, provided in paragraph (h) of this section, to submit evidence of eligible immigration
status if the family member:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Submits the declaration required under paragraph (e)(3) of this section certifying that any person for whom required
evidence has not been submitted is a noncitizen with eligible immigration status; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Certifies that the evidence needed to support a claim of eligible immigration status is temporarily unavailable,
additional time is needed to obtain and submit the evidence, and prompt and diligent efforts will be undertaken to
obtain the evidence.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Prohibition on indefinite extension period. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any extension of time, if granted, shall be for a specific period of time. The additional time provided should be sufficient
to allow the family the time to obtain the evidence needed. The IHA's determination of the length of the extension needed,
shall be based on the circumstances of the individual case.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Grant or denial of extension to be in writing. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The IHA's decision to grant or deny an extension as provided in paragraph (i)(1) of this section shall be issued to the
family by written notice. If the extension is granted, the notice shall specify the extension period granted. If the
extension is denied, the notice shall explain the reasons for denial of the extension.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(j) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Failure to submit evidence or establish eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If the family fails to submit required evidence of eligible immigration status within the time period specified in
the notice, or any extension granted in accordance with paragraph (i) of this section, or if the evidence is timely
submitted but fails to establish eligible immigration status, the IHA shall proceed to deny, prorate or terminate
assistance, or provide continued assistance or temporary deferral of termination of assistance, as appropriate,
in accordance, respectively with the provisions of paragraph (m) of this section or paragraph (r) of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(k) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Documents of eligible immigration status_
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 An IHA shall request and review original documents of eligible immigration status. The IHA shall retain photocopies
of the documents for its own records and return the original documents to the family.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Acceptable evidence of eligible immigration status.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The original of one of the following documents is acceptable evidence of eligible immigration status, subject to
verification in accordance with paragraph (l) of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Form I&hyph;551, Alien Registration Receipt Card (for permanent resident aliens);
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Form I&hyph;94, Arrival-Departure Record, with one of the following annotations:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) ``Admitted as Refugee Pursuant to Section 207'';
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) ``Section 208'' or ``Asylum'';
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) ``Section 243(h)'' or ``Deportation stayed by Attorney General'';
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) ``Paroled Pursuant to Sec. 212(d)(5) of the INA'';
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) If Form I&hyph;94, Arrival-Departure Record, is not annotated, then accompanied by one of the following documents:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) A final court decision granting asylum (but only if no appeal is taken);
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) A letter from an INS asylum officer granting asylum (if application is filed on or after October 1, 1990) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
or
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 from an INS district director granting asylum (if application filed before October 1, 1990);
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) A court decision granting withholding or deportation; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) A letter from an INS asylum officer granting withholding of deportation (if application filed on or after October
1, 1990).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
