(ii) For each child, the form must be signed by an adult member of the family residing in the assisted dwelling unit who
is responsible for the child. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by PHA. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The verification consent form shall provide that evidence of eligible immigration status may be released by the PHA,
without responsibility for the further use or transmission of the evidence by the entity receiving it, to: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) HUD as required by HUD; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The INS; and, if applicable; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Another Federal agency, or a State or local government agency in accordance with Federal, State or local law
that requires the release of the evidence to that agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice of release of evidence by HUD. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The verification consent form also shall notify the individual of the possible release of evidence of eligible immigration
status by HUD. Evidence of eligible immigration status shall only be released to the INS for purposes of establishing
eligibility for financial assistance and not for any other purpose. HUD is not responsible for the further use or transmission
of the evidence or other information by the INS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Individuals who do not contend to have eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If one or more members of a family elect not to contend that they have eligible immigration status and the other members
of the family establish their citizenship or eligible immigration status, the family may be considered for prorated
assistance under &sect;912.11 despite the fact that no declaration or documentation of eligible status is submitted
by one or more members of the family. The family must, however, identify to PHA the family member (or members) who will
elect not to contend that he or she has eligible immigration status. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notification of requirements of section 214. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Timing of notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by
this section, or to elect not to contend that one has eligible immigration status, as allowed by paragraph (e) of this
section, shall be given by the PHA as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicant's notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each applicant at the time
of application for financial assistance. Families whose applications are pending on [
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
insert the effective date of the final rule
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
] shall be notified of the requirements to submit evidence of eligible status as soon as possible after [
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
insert the effective date of the final rule
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Notice to families already receiving assistance. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For a family in occupancy on [
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
insert the effective date of the final rule
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
], notification of the requirement to submit evidence of eligible status shall be given to each at the time of, and together
with, the PHA's notice of the first regular reexamination after that date, but not later than one year following [
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
insert the effective date of the final rule
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
]. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Form and content of notice. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The notice shall: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) State that financial assistance is contingent upon the submission and verification, as appropriate, of the evidence
of citizenship or eligible immigration status, as required by this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Describe the type of evidence that must be submitted and state the time period in which that evidence must be submitted
(see paragraph (g) of this section concerning when evidence must be submitted); and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
