<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
, 112 S.Ct. 1011, 1015 (1992) (rejecting an interpretation that ``violates the settled rule that a statute must, if
possible, be construed in a fashion that every word has some operative effect'') (citation omitted); 
