Therefore, for example, Tribes meeting eligibility requirements for these provisions of the CAA would be treated
in the same manner as States in identifying what areas should be included in ``interstate'' air pollution and visibility
transport regions and in establishing commission membership. For eligible Tribes participating as members of such
