Also, treating Tribes in the same manner as States for purposes of section 505(a)(2) would require permitting authorities
under Title V to notify an eligible Tribe that is contiguous to a State in which an emission originates and whose air
quality may be affected by that emission, or that is within 50 miles of the emission source, of any Title V permit applications
that are forwarded to EPA.
