The regulations implementing the CAA span many pages of the Code of Federal Regulations. In today's action, EPA is
proposing to add new 40 CFR part 49, which will address the Tribal CAA authority described in this notice. To implement
this authority EPA is also proposing to add a general requirement in part 49 that eligible Tribes will be treated in
the same manner as States under all of EPA's existing, currently effective regulations implementing the Clean Air
Act, except those regulations implementing provisions of the CAA for which EPA has concluded that it would be inappropriate
to treat Tribes as States. Such exceptions are described in detail in Part III.B of this notice. 
